  {
    "type": "message",
    "subtype": "thread_broadcast",
    "text": "I want to switch from this one layout to this other layout. I got one key in a tiling manager. It either requires &gt;1 key with a stacking manager or it requires me to first create and save layouts. The reason it's easier in a tiling WM: somebody curated the layouts I'm likely to want in advance",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1566924145.158800",
    "thread_ts": "1566923504.141700",
    "root": {
      "client_msg_id": "f1e255ae-d5c9-40db-9699-2d9dd07be19b",
      "type": "message",
      "text": "And I haven't seen a reason you need less keyboard shortcuts with tiling?",
