  {
    "client_msg_id": "4efc9232-3a4b-4339-a2fc-3292cdcd2ec9",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "there's a saying from Runar Bjarnsson that \"constraints liberate; liberties constrain\". i've seen this play out in many different parts of life. for example, guitar is in some ways not as versatile as piano, but i find songwriting easier on guitar because it's easier to play within patterns. and sometime, ukulele is even easier to improvise on, despite being less powerful.\n\nbut on another topic, just as a suggestion, i try to be mindful of the extent to which i'm asking other people to do my thinking for me. as an outside observer, it reads a bit like you asking folks to drag you over the cognitive hill to get to the destination they reached on their own, while at the same time, being kind of resistant to getting there.",
    "user": "UKQT95T1V",
    "ts": "1566926972.205100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
